parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Seizure due to Oil Pump Gear Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic oil pump gear can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to a loss of control and potentially fatal accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or locks up suddenly
and may not restart after shutting off for a period of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the kickstand can cause the motorcycle to fall or roll while idling or parked, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The kickstand fails to keep the motorcycle upright
the motorcycle rolls or falls while idling or parked
the kickstand does not lock in place
the motorcycle is unstable on slight inclines.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Pump Failure with Plastic Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump with a plastic gear can cause the motorcycle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls while in operation

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump seam can cause fuel leaks onto the engine, which can lead to a fire, potentially resulting in serious injury or damage.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel pump
fuel dripping onto the engine or surrounding components.
